{#- ### Operational Strengths — categorical cluster view.
    Each row represents a STRENGTH CLUSTER (e.g. "Hardened HTTP Stack",
    "Authentication & Session Management") aggregating multiple fine-grained
    security_controls[] entries. Cluster definitions live in
    `data/strength-clusters.yaml`; the renderer (compose_threat_model.py
    → _build_strength_clusters) does the grouping deterministically.

    Filter rule (post-2026-05): only clusters with effectiveness ∈
    {adequate, partial} appear in this section. Weak-rated clusters are
    intentionally excluded — a control that is bypassed by Critical/High
    findings in its own remit is not an operational strength and surfacing
    it under this heading was semantically wrong. The demoted clusters
    remain in §6 Security Architecture where the section name matches.

    When the filter wipes the table entirely (every cluster demoted), the
    renderer passes an `empty_banner` italic-paragraph in lieu of an empty
    table. The banner names how many clusters were demoted so the section
    does not read as silently broken.

    Inputs:
      rows         — list of {label, what_in_place, effectiveness,
                     effectiveness_note, mitigates} where `what_in_place` is a
                     `<br/>`-joined compact list of the cluster's constituent
                     controls and `effectiveness_note` is the SUBSTANTIVE gap text
                     (empty for generic fillers) merged into the Effectiveness cell.
      overrides    — { intentionally_vulnerable_or_deficient, bottom_line }
      overflow_count — extra controls beyond the rendered cluster set (0 normally)
      show_intro / show_mitigates / section7_present — booleans
      empty_banner — italic paragraph rendered when `rows` is empty after the
                     strengths-only filter; empty string otherwise.
-#}
